<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, user-scalable=no, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <title>Simple session cookie example</title>
    <style>
        body {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: auto auto 75px auto;
            max-width: 40em;
            padding: 0 0 0 2em;
        }

        footer {
            font-style: italic;
            margin-top: 10em;
        }

        .host-banner {
            background-color: rgb(99, 36, 0);
            bottom: 0;
            left: 0;
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            width: 2em;
        }

        .host-banner[data-host="blue"] {
            background-color: rgb(28, 58, 114);
        }

        .host-banner[data-host="green"] {
            background-color: rgb(0, 82, 50);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<h1><a href="/">My Site Bros.</a></h1>
<h2>Simple session cookie example</h2>
<p>
    This page was sent from the server to your browser with a cookie.
    This was done by adding this HTTP response header:
</p>
<pre>Set-Cookie: simple-session=hello</pre>
<p>
    This is a simple session cookie example:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>a name: <code>simple-session</code></li>
    <li>and a value: <code>hello</code>.</li>
</ul>
<p>
    Because no date was specified, the cookie is supposed to expire at the end of the session.
    Which means when the browser is stopped.
</p>
<footer>
    A project by <a href="https://twitter.com/leroyj" target="_blank">@leroyj</a>.<br>
    derived from an initial project from <a href="https://twitter.com/hsablonniere" target="_blank">@hsablonniere</a>.
    Hosted on <a href="http://www.clever-cloud.com/">AWS</a>.
    Original sources on <a href="https://github.com/hsablonniere/cookies.rocks" target="_blank">Github</a>.
</footer>
<div class="host-banner" data-host="<%= host %>"></div>
</body>
</html>
